<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-479-938  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 479 938.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Macworld  July 1990 v7 n7 p23(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Is your computer killing you? (Commentary) (column)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Borrell, Jerry.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Health hazards from the extremely low frequency (ELF) magneticfields emitted by computer monitors are an increasing concern.andO;The problems faced by today's computer workers are analogous tothose faced by factory workers and miners in the 1890s, whenunhealthy working conditions caused such diseases as black lung.andO;Every claim of impact on health has begun with long periods ofdenial, followed by periods when terminology clouds issues.andO;Various parties eventually agree on terminology, but diseasesufferers are seldom able to describe the mechanism by which theirworking conditions cause their medical conditions.andP;  ELF emissionsare suspected of causing immune deficiencies, interference withintracellular activities, and hormonal disturbances.andP;  Governmentleaders currently are reluctant to discuss the problem, andmonitor manufacturers deny that any danger exists.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     MicrocomputersHealthCancer.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>